equals(Object) - Method in class node.sharedMemory.DetectionFrequencyIp
If object is a DetectionFrequencyIp object, this makes sure that the addresses match
If object is an InetAddress, this makes sure that the address matches the detected address
Else this behaves the same as Object.equals.
equals(Object) - Method in class node.sharedMemory.DetectionFrequencyString
If object is a DetectionFrequencyString object, this makes sure that the string pattern matches.
If object is a StringPattern object, this makes sure that the string pattern matches.
If object is a String, this makes sure that the string matches the one in the string pattern.
Else this behaves the same as Object.equals.
equals(Object) - Method in class node.sharedMemory.InterfaceAddressStats
Checks if the addresses match for InterfaceAddressStats and InetAddress arguments
Returns true for null arguments
Otherwise is the same as Object.equals
equals(Object) - Method in class node.sharedMemory.InterfaceStatistics
If the object is an InterfaceStatistics, then this returns true if their names match.
If the object is a String, then this returns true if the String matches the name of this interface.
Otherwise acts the same as Object.equals
equals(Object) - Method in class node.sharedMemory.StringPattern
If the object is a StringPattern, it checks if the pattern of the two StringPatterns strings match
If the object is a String, it checks if the pattern in StringPattern matches the string
If the object is an InetAddress, it checks if any of the IP addresses associated with this pattern match the provided IP address.
